OGG file with the features:
Digital rights management: OGG files do not support digital rights management (DRM) restrictions, making them ideal for open distribution and sharing.
Chapter support: OGG files can contain chapter markers for easy navigation within long audio tracks or podcasts.
High-resolution audio: OGG files can support high-resolution audio formats such as 24-bit and 96kHz for audiophile-quality playback.
ReplayGain support: OGG files can store ReplayGain information to normalize audio playback volume across tracks.